    <h2 id="introduction">Introduction</h2>
    <p>The PataNgoma Audio Tagger is a powerful command-line tool that allows you to enhance your music library's metadata by fetching and updating tags from popular music databases like MusicBrainz, Deezer, and Spotify. This tool provides a rich and seamless CLI experience, making it easy to organize and manage your music collection effortlessly.</p>

    <img src="screenshot.png" alt="Screenshot of the Music Audio Tagger">

    <h2 id="features">Features</h2>
    <ul>
        <li>Fetch and update metadata tags for your music files.</li>
        <li>Seamlessly integrate with MusicBrainz, Deezer, and Spotify for accurate and comprehensive tag information.</li>
        <li>A user-friendly CLI that provides a smooth and efficient tagging process.</li>
        <li>Customize and configure the tool to suit your specific music library needs.</li>
        <li>Supports various audio file formats, ensuring compatibility with your music collection.</li>
    </ul>

